---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Build Your Talent" description="Develop AI skills inside your healthcare organization through certified Microsoft training, cohort-based programs, and hands-on workshops designed for healthcare professionals.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-inner page-hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <div class="hero-badge">Build</div>
        <h1>Build Your AI Talent</h1>
        <p>Your staff already has potential. They already use Microsoft 365. They already make decisions with data. They just haven't been trained on the AI tools sitting right in front of them. Scale Street's Build services change that through certified Microsoft training, cohort programs, and hands-on workshops designed for healthcare professionals.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-image">
        <img src="/images/healthcare-tech.jpg" alt="Healthcare technology training" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Build -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner why-build">
      <p>The AI talent gap in healthcare isn't about hiring data scientists. It's about training your quality coordinator to build a Power BI dashboard. It's about teaching your clinic manager to use Copilot to draft patient communications. It's about showing your revenue cycle team how Power Automate can cut manual work in half.</p>
      <p>Scale Street's training is delivered by a Microsoft Certified Trainer with a Ph.D. in healthcare management, not a generic tech instructor reading slides. Every program is built for the reality of healthcare operations: short timeframes, real workflows, and staff who can't afford to step away for a week.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Scale Street Training Programs -->
  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Scale Street Training Programs</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="intro-text">These are Scale Street's own programs, designed specifically for healthcare organizations. Unlike standard Microsoft courses that cram content into 1-3 intensive days, our programs are built around healthcare workflows, use real-world examples from clinical and operational settings, and are delivered by a Microsoft Certified Trainer with a Ph.D. in healthcare management.</p>

      <div class="programs-grid">
        <div class="program-card">
          <div class="card-accent blue"></div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Understanding AI</h3>
            <div class="program-format">Half day (4 hours) &middot; Virtual or on-site &middot; Interactive workshop</div>
            <p>A foundational program for healthcare professionals who want to understand what AI is, how it works, and what it means for their organization. No technical background required. This course cuts through the hype and gives your team a clear, practical understanding of AI concepts, terminology, capabilities, and limitations so they can participate in AI conversations with confidence.</p>
            <div class="card-meta">
              <span class="best-for">Best for:</span> All staff levels. Ideal as a starting point for organizations beginning their AI journey.
            </div>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request Information <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="program-card">
          <div class="card-accent green"></div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>AI for Clinical Leaders</h3>
            <div class="program-format">Full day (6 hours) &middot; Virtual or on-site &middot; Interactive workshop</div>
            <p>Designed for clinical leadership, this program focuses on how AI tools (including Microsoft 365 Copilot) can reduce documentation burden, support clinical decision-making, improve patient communication, and streamline care coordination. Clinical leaders leave with a clear picture of where AI fits into their workflows and how to champion adoption within their teams.</p>
            <div class="card-meta">
              <span class="best-for">Best for:</span> Chief Nursing Officers, Medical Directors, Department Heads, Clinical Managers, and clinical staff leading AI adoption efforts.
            </div>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request Information <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="program-card">
          <div class="card-accent mint"></div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>AI for Tech Leaders</h3>
            <div class="program-format">Full day (6 hours) &middot; Virtual or on-site &middot; Interactive workshop</div>
            <p>Built for the IT and informatics professionals responsible for deploying, configuring, and supporting AI tools across the organization. Covers Microsoft 365 Copilot administration, Power Platform governance, tenant security, data protection, and adoption monitoring. This program prepares your technical team to manage AI infrastructure confidently and securely.</p>
            <div class="card-meta">
              <span class="best-for">Best for:</span> CIOs, IT Directors, Health Informatics leads, and technical staff managing Microsoft environments.
            </div>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request Information <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cohort Section -->
  <section class="section bg-blue">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cohort-grid">
        <div class="cohort-content">
          <div class="cohort-badge">Featured Program</div>
          <h2>12-Week AI Readiness Cohort for Rural Hospitals</h2>
          <p class="cohort-partner">In partnership with HomeTown Health</p>
          <p>Scale Street delivers the Artificial Intelligence Readiness Program for Rural Healthcare, a 12-week cohort experience designed to bring rural health organizations together to build AI readiness as a group.</p>
          <p>The cohort includes weekly training sessions, resources and guides, and seats in the AI-PRH Certification (the first and only AI certification built specifically for rural health professionals). Led by Dr. Tyler Wallace, this program gives rural hospital teams a structured path from "we know we should be doing something with AI" to a clear, actionable plan.</p>
          <div class="cohort-meta">
            <span class="best-for-light">Best for:</span> Rural hospitals and critical access hospitals looking for a structured, peer-supported approach to AI adoption.
          </div>
          <a href="https://hometownhealthonline.com/ruralhealthai/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-white" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Learn More at HomeTown Health <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
        </div>
        <div class="cohort-visual">
          <img src="/images/rural-hospital.jpg" alt="Rural hospital training cohort" class="cohort-image" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Official Microsoft Courseware -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Official Microsoft Courseware</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="intro-text">Scale Street also delivers official Microsoft training courses (Microsoft Official Curriculum) through our Microsoft Certified Trainer. These are the same standardized courses offered by training partners worldwide, following Microsoft's defined curriculum, materials, and lab environments.</p>
      <p class="intro-text" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">The difference: when you take an official Microsoft course through Scale Street, your instructor is a healthcare strategist who contextualizes every module for clinical and operational workflows, not a generalist reading slides to a room full of IT professionals from random industries.</p>

      <div class="courses-grid">
        <div class="course-card">
          <div class="course-code">AB-730T00</div>
          <h3>Transform Business Workflows with Generative AI</h3>
          <p>Learn how to use Microsoft 365 Copilot to improve daily work, drive business outcomes, and make informed decisions. Covers practical Copilot usage across Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, and Teams, along with responsible AI principles, prompt management, and agent use cases. No technical background required.</p>
          <div class="course-duration">1 day, instructor-led</div>
        </div>

        <div class="course-card">
          <div class="course-code">AB-900T00</div>
          <h3>Introduction to Microsoft 365 and AI Administration</h3>
          <p>Covers foundational Microsoft 365 services, identity and access management, data protection and governance, Copilot administration (licensing, configuration, adoption monitoring), and agent creation and management. Designed for IT staff and administrators supporting Copilot-enabled environments.</p>
          <div class="course-duration">1 day, instructor-led</div>
        </div>

        <div class="course-card">
          <div class="course-code">PL-300T00</div>
          <h3>Design and Manage Analytics Solutions Using Power BI</h3>
          <p>The official preparation course for the PL-300 certification exam. Covers data preparation, modeling, visualization, analysis, and deployment in Power BI. Designed for analysts and reporting professionals who need to build dashboards, automate reporting, and deliver data-driven insights.</p>
          <div class="course-duration">3 days, instructor-led</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="courses-notes">
        <p>Additional courses available on request. If your organization needs a course not listed here, let us know. As an MCT, we can deliver any official Microsoft course that maps to our held certifications.</p>
        <p>All official courses include post-training achievement codes for participants. Private sessions for your organization or open enrollment options available.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request a Course <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Comparison Section -->
  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Which format is right for you?</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="compare-grid">
        <div class="compare-card">
          <div class="compare-accent blue"></div>
          <div class="compare-body">
            <h3>Choose a Scale Street program if</h3>
            <p>your team needs healthcare-specific training designed for clinical or operational leaders, with content built around real healthcare workflows and AI use cases. Best for organizations that want their people to understand AI in the context of their actual work.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-card">
          <div class="compare-accent green"></div>
          <div class="compare-body">
            <h3>Choose official Microsoft courseware if</h3>
            <p>your team needs standardized Microsoft curriculum, certification preparation with official materials, or your organization requires courses that follow Microsoft's defined structure. Best for staff pursuing Microsoft certifications or organizations with compliance requirements around training standards.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-card highlight">
          <div class="compare-accent mint"></div>
          <div class="compare-body">
            <h3>Not sure?</h3>
            <p>Most of our healthcare clients start with our custom programs (Understanding AI, AI for Clinical Leaders, or AI for Tech Leaders) and add official courseware when staff are ready to pursue certifications. We can help you map the right path.</p>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Schedule a Call <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Network Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner network-section">
      <div class="network-grid">
        <div class="network-content">
          <h2>Train Your Entire Network</h2>
          <p>If you're a PCA, HCCN, or health center network, you don't have to solve the AI talent gap one member at a time. Scale Street delivers cohort-based training across your member organizations so your network gets consistent AI skills development with one contract and one partner.</p>
          <p>How it works: we design a training program matched to your members' needs and tech stack. Your members enroll together in cross-organization cohorts. You manage one relationship. We manage enrollment, delivery, and outcomes reporting. Network arrangements available across all Build programs.</p>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Let's Design a Network Program <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
        </div>
        <div class="network-visual">
          <img src="/images/community-health.jpg" alt="Health center network training" class="network-image" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="section cta-section">
    <div class="section-inner section-center">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Not sure which program fits?</h2>
        <p>Every organization starts somewhere different. Let's have a quick conversation about your team's current skills, your tech stack, and your goals, and we'll recommend the right starting point.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Schedule a Call <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .page-hero {
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem 3rem;
    background: var(--color-white);
  }

  .page-hero-inner {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-hero-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .hero-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-blue);
    background: rgba(15, 15, 189, 0.07);
    padding: 0.375rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .page-hero p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .hero-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 400px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 20px;
  }

  /* Why Build */
  .why-build {
    max-width: 780px;
  }

  .why-build p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-600);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  /* Shared */
  .bg-light {
    background: var(--color-gray-50);
  }

  .bg-blue {
    background: var(--color-blue);
    color: var(--color-white);
  }

  .cta-section {
    background: var(--color-gray-50);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .intro-text {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 780px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  /* Program Cards */
  .programs-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .program-card {
    display: flex;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--color-white);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-gray-200);
    border-radius: 16px;
    transition: box-shadow 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }

  .program-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .card-accent {
    width: 6px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .card-accent.blue { background: var(--color-blue); }
  .card-accent.green { background: var(--color-green); }
  .card-accent.mint { background: var(--color-blue-light); }

  .card-body {
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .card-body h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .card-body p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .card-meta {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .best-for {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-dark);
  }

  .program-format {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-blue);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* Cohort */
  .cohort-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .cohort-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
    padding: 0.375rem 0.875rem;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .cohort-content h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--color-white);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .cohort-partner {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .cohort-content p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cohort-meta {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .best-for-light {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-white);
  }

  .cohort-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 400px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 20px;
    border: 3px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
  }

  /* Course Cards */
  .courses-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .course-card {
    background: var(--color-gray-50);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-gray-200);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    transition: box-shadow 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }

  .course-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .course-code {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--color-blue);
    background: rgba(15, 15, 189, 0.07);
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .course-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .course-card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .course-duration {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-gray-600);
  }

  .courses-notes {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .courses-notes p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  /* Comparison */
  .compare-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .compare-card {
    display: flex;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--color-white);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-gray-200);
    border-radius: 16px;
    transition: box-shadow 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }

  .compare-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .compare-card.highlight {
    border-color: var(--color-blue-light);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--color-blue-light);
  }

  .compare-accent {
    width: 6px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .compare-accent.blue { background: var(--color-blue); }
  .compare-accent.green { background: var(--color-green); }
  .compare-accent.mint { background: var(--color-blue-light); }

  .compare-body {
    padding: 1.75rem;
  }

  .compare-body h3 {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .compare-body p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Network */
  .network-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .network-content h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .network-content p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .network-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 360px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 20px;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-hero {
      padding: 3.5rem 1.25rem 2.5rem;
    }

    .page-hero-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .page-hero h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .hero-image img {
      height: 260px;
    }

    .cohort-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2.5rem;
    }

    .cohort-image {
      height: 260px;
    }

    .courses-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .compare-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .network-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2.5rem;
    }

    .network-image {
      height: 240px;
    }
  }
</style>
